@node v4_24 "CINS v4.24 (Nov 26 1999)"


Changes from v4.23 (Nov 26 1999) are:

ALL:
* Any and all keyfile checks removed.  CINS no longer requires registration.

@endnode

@node v4_23 "CINS v4.23 (Mar 26 1999)"


Changes from v4.22 (Aug 16 1998) are:

ALL:
* Fixed the version string to be more in line with standards.
* Removed hardcoded 'splash text' in all programs.
* Removed all CNet/3 specific code.  CNet/3 is no longer supported with CINS.
  With CNet/5 now in testing, doesn't make sense to try and keep 3 different
  versions up and running.
* CNetC calls changed to use cnetc.library (as ditching CNet/3 code let me do
  this finally).

CINSConfig:
* Cleaned up the Account page to have more descriptive names for the fields.

CINSWeb:
* Now sets default user web dir appropriate to the CNet version used.

CINS.acc:
* Distribution copy of this file was in the old format.  Fixed.

CINS.cfg:
* Updated the defaults to more current sites.

Contrib/Telnet-4.x.lha:
* Updated again to use the new DOECHO command line option to Ctelnet for MUDs.

@endnode

@node v4_22 "CINS v4.22 (Aug 16 1998)"


Changes from v4.21 (Jul 28 1998) are:

CINS:
* Cleaned up output on telnet/ftp/archie/irc site selection.  No longer
  offers Next/Previous if there isn't anything to go Next/Previous to.

CINS.txt:
* Added lines 195-199 to cleanup site menu displays.

CINS.guide:
* Updated clients section with current CNet utility status.

Contrib/CINS.cmd-4.x:
* CINS.cmd file preset with CNet/4 utilities.

Contrib/Telnet-4.x.lha:
* Telnet data files tweaked to work better with Ctelnet.  However, MUD
  connections will require the workaround as stated in the @{" Utilities " link Utilities}
  section.

@endnode

@node v4_21 "CINS v4.21 (Jul 28 1998)"


Changes from v4.20 (Jan  4 1998) are:

ALL:
* Minor code changes for better OS compatibility.

@endnode

@node v4_20 "CINS v4.20 (Jan  4 1998)"


Changes from v4.19a (Jan  1 1998) are:

ALL:
* Fixed a possible problem in the text load sequence which could cause
  numerous illegal memory accesses in certain specific conditions.

CINSConfig:
* Manual bbstext line configuration is no longer needed.  CINS will figure
  this one out on itself now.  GUI and VDE elements removed.
  @{b}NOTE!@{ub}: The bbstext line MUST have "CINS Stuff" in it somewhere
  for this to function correctly.

CINSEdit:
* Now handles writing of the user config VDE itself.
@endnode

@node v4_19a "CINS v4.19a (Jan  1 1998)"


Changes from v4.19 (Dec 29 1997) are:

ALL:
* Configuration load functions in the link library were not recompiled after
  the last source change.  This could cause odd accounting results.  Fixed.
* Copyright dates adjusted.

CINS:
* Minor internal modifications.

CINSMaint:
* Now using an alternate method of determining high account number.
@endnode

@node v4_19 "CINS v4.19 (Dec 29 1997)"


Changes from v4.18 (Dec 14 1997) are:

ALL:
* Fixed a longstanding oddity in the display routine dealing with screen
  menus.  CINS was looking for just MenuName, and not (sys|tt?).MenuName.

CINSConfig:
* Minor VDE error corrected.
* Purge days for FTP files is now in the Accounting window.  This is
  now set on an access group by access group basis.
* Purge days for FTP files removed from the VDE.
* Minor GUI rearrangement to conform to Style Guide suggestions.

CINSMaint:
* Now works on files based on the new purge days settings.

CINS419:
* Update executable to grow CINS.acc to allow for further expansion, as
  well as copying over purge days from the global settings.
@endnode

@node v4_18 "CINS v4.18 (Dec 14 1997)"


Changes from v4.17 (Dec 13 1997) are:

CINS:
* Now uses defaults for new users as specified in CINSConfig.
* Menuing not working correctly with a number of entries equal to 1+9n
  (10, 19,etc) fixed.

CINSConfig:
* You can now specify user default configuration options for FTP and CINS.
* VDE now has options for user defaults.

CINSDir:
* Fixed a problem with downloads removing items from the filelist.
* Now uses defaults for new users as specified in CINSConfig.

CINSEdit:
* Now uses defaults for new users as specified in CINSConfig.

CINSWeb:
* Fixed a problem with downloads removing items from the filelist.
* Fixed problem with naming a new file the same as an old file, and having
  it duplicate the entry in the filelist.

CINS418:
* Update executable to clean out old junk in the CINS.cfg file.  It is
  HIGHLY recommended that you run this file.
@endnode

@node v4_17 "CINS v4.17 (Dec 13 1997)"


Changes from v4.16 (Dec  8 1997) are:

ALL:
* Changed configuration loading procedure, so RAM usage should be a little
  less.

CINS:
* IRC was using the description of the server as the hostname.  Fixed.

CINS, CINSDir and CINSWeb:
* You can now override the directory usage limits on a user-by-user basis.
  See the @{" _CINSUserLimit " link _CINSUserLimit} and @{" _CINSWebLimit " link _CINSWebLimit} sections for details.

CINSConfig:
* Minor GUI oddities fixed.
* Potential shutdown error in low memory situations.  Fixed
* Limit on bbstext and bbsmenus in the VDE were too low.  Fixed.
@endnode

@node v4_16 "CINS v4.16 (Dec  8 1997)"


Changes from v4.15 (Nov 23 1997) are:

CINS, CINSDir and CINSWeb:
* All executables will now exit when a user chooses to logoff from within the
  program. (Off BBS command)

CINS:
* Fixed a truckload of Enforcer hits that cropped up if there was a problem
  in the startup initialization. (failure to open bsdsocket.library, CINS.txt,
  etc.)
* Some internal data restructuring to make the code a bit more modular, and
  easier to handle in regards to future additions.

CINSAccounting:
* Go figure.. everytime I make something little to add on to Config, I end
  up making it internal the next revision.  CINSAccounting may now be deleted
  as it has become part of CINSConfig.

CINSConfig:
* Now contains the functionality of CINSAccounting.
* Archie, FTP, IRC, and Telnet menu data is now editable from within the GUI.

cins.library:
* Library revision bumped to 4.16.  Now includes routines for inserting entries
  to CINS internal data lists.  (not really important outside of my use..
  at the moment.  =)
@endnode

@node v4_15 "CINS v4.15 (Nov 23 1997)"


Changes from v4.14 (Nov  8 1997) are:

CINS:
* Now will work with CNetIRC's new argument handling in CNet/4.34+.
* Will no longer be able to bring up an "Insert Volume XXX:" requestor.
* AddToDB option will now work with Miami 2.92c and above.  However,
  it will bring up a requestor alerting you to the changes about to be
  made to the user DB at Miami load time, or if it is issued a CHANGEDB
  REXX command.

CINSAccounting & CINSConfig:
* Now using BGUI for layout.  Makes my life alot easier on the GUI side, as
  well as making it more flexible.

CINS.txt:
* Minor changes to lines 35 and 45.
@endnode

@node v4_14 "CINS v4.14 (Nov  8 1997)"


Changes from v4.13 (Oct 12 1997) are:

ALL:
* Accounting values are now set by ACCESS GROUP!  It is highly suggested that
  you run the including CINS414 executable in the Convert directory to carry
  over any accounting data from your CINS main configuration.  All modules
  using any accounting code now use the new setup.

CINS:
* CNet/3 version will now give users an 'out' if they don't want to change
  their UUCP ID from a number.  They can now choose to exit CINS instead of
  being consigned to a life in EP. =)
* Menus not refreshing properly after a selection has been fixed.

CINSAccounting:
* New executable to handle accounting details.

CINSConfig:
* Several GUI/VDE elements removed/disabled as they are now controlled by
  CINSAccounting.

CINSDir:
* ANSI mode wasn't displaying directory size correctly.  Fixed.

CINS.txt:
* Lines 188-194 added for cleaner menu output.
@endnode

@node v4_13 "CINS v4.13 (Oct 12 1997)"


Changes from v4.12 (Sep 23 1997) are:

ALL:
* Interesting load conflict possible if cnet.library wasn't available.
  Fixed.

CINS:
* Now adds the user to the appropriate database file for the TCP stack you are
  running.  AmiTCP:db/passwd for AmiTCP and Miami/Database/Users for Miami.
  This only takes effect if you enable the Add Users to DB option in CINSConfig.
  (NOTE: Miami currently does not allow for additions to Database/Users via
   the only method I know of for Miami.  This may change in future versions
   of Miami)
* Potentially interesting situation at shutdown, in which I shut a lib, and
  then used a function in it.  Would only be a real problem if all instances
  of cnet.library were closed (neat trick with bbs loaded).  Fixed.
* FTP/Telnet submenus were displaying wrong due to a modification I made in
  CINS 4.12 to data handling.

CINSConfig:
* Add users to DB option added to GUI and VDE.

CINSDir:
* Displays used space in KB or MB depending on amount of space used.

CINSWeb:
* Displays used space in KB or MB depending on amount of space used.
* Displays the filename of the file being edited in the Visual Editor now.

CINS.txt:
* Modification of line 54 to fix FTP/Telnet submenu display.
* Modification to line 113 to fix a display oddity in the IRC menus.
* Addition of lines 185-187 for KB/MB display in CINSDir/CINSWeb.
* Addition of lines 183-184 for User DB additions.

cins.library:
* Much of the site data handling code has been moved into a shared library.
  CINS executables have a slight size change due to this, and the memory
  footprint at execution should be even less now.  This file should remain in
  CINS:Libs!!!

@endnode

@node v4_12 "CINS v4.12 (Sep 23 1997)"


Changes from v4.11 (Sep  5 1997) are:

ALL:
* Major code modularization.  This should cut down on executable size a tad,
  and makes my life easier on code maintenance.

CINS:
* Addition of Web to the bbsmenu.
* Addition of 'W' to the hotkey interface to allow access to the Web Maint.
* Sanity check added for the number of entries in CINS.cmd.  Previously CINS
  could lockup if all entries were not present.

CINSConfig:
* Added Window size gadget.  When working with fonts > 10 point, the default
  size wasn't quite enough to show everything.  (thank my new 1200/060 and
  multisync monitor for that one).
* Added gadget for CINSWeb limits.
* VDE change for CINSWeb limits.

CINSWeb:
* New user maintenance module to allow your users to modify and maintain their
  own web pages.

CINS.cmd:
* Addition of entry 16 for CINSWeb.

CINS.txt:
* Changes to line 30, 138, 162 and 163 to account for CINSWeb.
* Additions of lines 178-181 for CINSWeb.
@endnode

@node v4_11 "CINS v4.11 (Sep  5 1997)"


Changes from v4.10 (Aug 22 1997) are:

CINS:
* Enforcer hit at start found and squished.
* Notebooks now save at menu exit, whether it be due to selecting a site
  or quitting the menu.
* Notebooks now implemented for FTP, Telnet and IRC.

CINS.txt:
* Change to line 117 to fix a long standing coding annoyance.
* Lines 172-177 added for notebook entry additional support.
@endnode

@node v4_10 "CINS v4.10 (Aug 22 1997)"


Changes from v4.9a (Jun 30 1997) are:

CINS:
* Some internal data handling redone a bit.
* User notebooks added for Archie. (FTP, Telnet and IRC in the next revision).
* Problem at exit with memory flushing which could crop up in some cases
  resolved.
* Menuing system was one entry off from the input.

CINS.txt:
* Changes to lines 55-56 to add notebook commands.
* Change to line 107 for manual Archie/IRC entries.
* Addition of lines 164-171 for notebook additions.
@endnode

@node v4_9a "CINS v4.9a (Jun 30 1997)"


Changes from v4.9 (Jun 27 1997) are:

CINS:
* Now uses some new functions of the CNet 4.28 cnet.library.  CNet 4.28+ is
  @{b}REQUIRED@{ub} for the CNet/4 version.

CINSDir:
* Now uses some new functions of the CNet 4.28 cnet.library.  CNet 4.28+ is
  @{b}REQUIRED@{ub} for the CNet/4 version.

CINS.cfg:
* Updated binary config file now included in the distribution archive.

CINS48:
* Error fixed in the conversion utility that would drop the value of the old
  LINE configuration directive.

@endnode

@node v4_9 "CINS v4.9 (Jun 27 1997)"


Changes from v4.8 (May 19 1997) are:

CINS:
* The menu size limits are GONE!  No 64 menu limit, or 16 IRC server limits.
  All menu data is dynamically stored.

CINS.txt:
* Changes to lines 145 and 122 to cleanup CINSDir display a bit.

CINSDir:
* Removal of the old static array setup for file display in the ANSI mode.
  Now uses a exec.library list structure to mean no limit to files listed,
  but for your available RAM.
* Load should be significantly faster in the ANSI mode.  The two directory
  scans have been combined into one, as well as the old method of re-reading
  the whole directory after every action has been removed.

@endnode

@node v4_8 "CINS v4.8 (May 19 1997)"


Changes from v4.7c (internal) are:

**IMPORTANT**

    You MUST run the program "CINS48" in the CINS/Convert directory.  This
will rewrite your configuration file in the packed format.

ALL:
* Changes to utilize the packed datafile format of the primary
  configuration file.

CINSConfig:
* GUI elements added (disabled) for Telnet/FTP/Archie/IRC editing.
@endnode

@node v4_7c "CINS v4.7c (internal)"


Changes from v4.7b (May  5 1997) are:

CINS:
* No longer complains about the lack of an IRC menu.  Now it'll silently
  execute the defined client with the associated defaults.

CINSConfig:
* Basic font sensitivity added.  Now uses the default screen font.  If this is
  not an 8 point font, you may have some display oddities.
@endnode

@node v4_7b "CINS v4.7b"


Changes from v4.7a (May  2 1997) are:

CINS:
* Stupid typo could prevent keyfiles from working.  Ooops.
* Code for 4.x version's check for $HOME:.netrc changed to use a cnet.library
  call instead of an ANSI C call.  4.x version should now be a bit smaller.

CINSDir:
* Stupid dependancy on $HOME:.netrc removed.  They don't really need that
  for this program after all.

CINSEdit:
* Code for 4.x version's check for $HOME:.netrc changed to use a cnet.library
  call instead of an ANSI C call.  4.x version should now be a bit smaller.
@endnode

@node v4_7a "CINS v4.7a"


Changes from v4.7 (May  1 1997) are:

CINS, CINSDir, and CINSEdit:
* Minor code corrections fixing something that would have been broken had
  the compiler done things just a wee bit differently.

CINSCfg:
* GONE!  All functionality is now available in the combo VDE/GUI CINSConfig.

CINSConfig:
* Added in VDE handling.  Now will run with VDE when from CNet, GUI otherwise.
  GUI also updates the CINS VDE's when run.

CINS.cmd:
* Updated the command line for CINSConfig to point to CINSConfig, and not
  CINSCfg.
@endnode

@node v4_7 "CINS v4.7"


Changes from v4.6 (Apr  7 1997) are:

CINSCfg:
* A slew of little updates and bugfixes.  Most notably the accurate reading
  of the DAYS directive from the CINS.cfg file.

CINSConfig:
* New GUI Configuration utility for CINS.
@endnode

@node v4_6 "CINS v4.6"


Changes from v4.5 (Feb 17 1997) are:

(note: the long delay between this version and the last is due to loads of
 work, moving, and toying with some other projects I had been neglecting.
 Those of you who know me in IRC, know about those projects.  =)

ALL:
* Numerous little optimizations across all files.

CINS:
* Lack of an IRC menu will drop directly into the IRC executable with
  the default server defined in CINS.cfg.
* If bsdsocket.library is not available, CINS will exit out at start with a
  statement to that effect.

CINSCfg:
* Now displays the serial number of your CINS version in the VDE.

CINSDir:
* No longer requires bbsmenu CINS.cfg/MENU + 1.  This functionality has been
  replaced by leeching bbsmenu #4 for parsing.
@endnode

@node v4_5 "CINS v4.5"


Changes from v4.4 (Feb 13 1997) are:

ALL:
* FDIR directive now has a %s in it to be substituted by the user's UUCP id.
  This change was reflected across all modules.  This will allow for paths
  such as Mail:Users/%s/Files.
@endnode

@node v4_4 "CINS v4.4"


Changes from v4.3 (Jan 26 1997) are:

ALL:
* Changed memory handling a tad.
* Minor code tweaks.

CINSDir:
* Tag option in the hotkey mode now allows for the command '*' to tag all
  visible files.

CINS.txt:
* Line 139 changed to reflect new option to tag.
@endnode

@node v4_3 "CINS v4.3"


Changes from v4.2 (Jan 22 1997) are:


CINSCfg:
* CD flag added to disable the shell CD in CINSDir.

CINSDir:
* ANSI mode added.  This is still early, so may have some problems.
* CD command disable-able from CINSCfg.

CINSEdit:
* CD command toggle, and ANSI dirmaint options added to the VDEs and text
  interface.

CINS.txt:
* Lines 143-145 added to support the new hotkey dirmaint options.
@endnode

@node v4_2 "CINS v4.2"


Changes from v4.1 (Jan 19 1997) are:

ALL:
* Now using CNet's internal version of several structs I was using.  This
  results in a smaller RAM footprint, and a slightly smaller executable.
* Minor additional optimizations across all modules, with more creative use
  of pointers.

CINSDir:
* Preliminary code for the ANSI version of the DirMaint utility added.
  This does not work currently, it's still in development, so don't try it.
* Now reports the proper directory size for all files the user's directory
  and all subdirectories of it. (CNet/4 only)

CINS.txt:
* Lines 139-142 added to support the preliminary coding of the ANSI dir
  maint utility.
@endnode

@node v4_1 "CINS v4.1"


Changes from v2.14 (Jan  7 1997) are:

CINS:
* Now handles pre-existing .netrc files better.
* Lack of carrier check in menuing code fixed.
* Changes to user prefs from within CINS now affect the current session.
  Previous behavior was to take effect on the following use of CINS. (Fate)
* First Public RELEASE version for CNet/3 and CNet/4.

CINSDir:
* Security hole with the CD command where users could change below their
  home dir if the name for the UserDir was a device name and not a volume
  name found and fixed. (Fate)
* Problem found with output sending the wrong data in several places.
  Fixed.

CINSEdit:
* Users may now specify a nick for IRC which will bypass the nick question
  if they do have one set.

CINS.txt:
* Change to line 7 to accomodate the prompt change for the shell mode and
  DirMaint.  (Fate)
* Changes to lines 162, 163 to accomodate the new IRC Nick preference
  option.
@endnode

@node v2_14 "CINS v2.14"


Changes from v2.13 (Dec 23 1996) are:

CINS:
* Account balance display now works.
* Now recalls prefs against all ports when doing a Muffle All directive.
* Entering the last item of a Telnet/FTP menu would not work.  Fixed.
* Archie and IRC now use the new menuing system.  All instances of the old
  menuing code should now be gone.
* IRC used to claim the default server was the first one in the server list.
  Should have reported the default server listed in CINS.cfg.  Fixed.
* More internal variable rearrangement to Archie and IRC variables.

CINSDir:
* Wildcard support for the Download, Delete, Dir, List and * functions added.
* Now checks for the presence of a ! in the command line for delete
  functions, and will now delete without question if one is present.

CINS.txt:
* Minor change to lines 103, 105 to support new menuing system in Archie.
* Minor change to line 114 to support the new menu system in IRC.
* Minor change to line 128.
* Lines 135-137 added to support balance display.
@endnode

@node v2_13 "CINS v2.13"


Changes from v2.12 (Dec 19 1996) are:

ALL:
* Found a lurking printf() in all files.  Changed it to a Printf() and
  everything shrunk about 2.5k.  You won't see me complaining.  <grin>

CINS:
* Logging wouldn't report time used if there was no rate set.  Fixed.
* Changed handling of FTP/Telnet entries and menus to facilitate possible
  VDE/GUI configuration in the future.
* Minor alterations to internal variable handling.
* Auto-Muffle should be a little smarter.  Used to un-muffle a person on
  exit if they entered CINS muffled with the Muffle All config flag set.
* Menuing system recode begun.  Telnet/FTP menu/submenus now use the new
  system.

CINSCfg:
* New configuration option to specify how many days before a file is purged
  from a user directory.
* VDE layout rearranged for future expansion.

CINSDir:
* Potential security issues, and just general possible problems avoided by
  denying access to 'dot' files for read/delete.  Also now will notify the
  use if the file specified for those functions is not found.
* List and Dir no longer display '.' files.  The user should not have
  anything to do with them in most cases.  In those that they should, a
  method of editing them will be provided.

CINSEdit:
* Minor alterations to internal variable handling.

CINSMaint:
* No longer accepts command line arguments.  Configuration options for
  CINSMaint are controlled by CINSCfg.

CINS.txt:
* Lines 55 and 56 changed to accomodate the new menuing system's command
  set.
* Line 58 removed.
@endnode

@node v2_12 "CINS v2.12"


Changes from v2.11 (Dec 18 1996) are:

CINS:
* FTP directory limits instituted in main executable.
* Logging facility for CINS usage and cost instituted.

CINSCfg:
* New Config options:
  * Allow user FTP uploads?
  * Log ID for Config logging.
  * Space quotas for user FTP directories.

CINSDir:
* Code added to warn users when their maximum directory size is reached.
* Upload restriction code installed.

CINSMaint:
* Now uses ReadArgs() for argument handling.  You can supply a ? as an
  argument to get the command template.  (Currently only "DAYS/A/N").
* Other minor code optimizations.

CINS.txt:
* Line 120 added for logging purposes.
* Line 123 added for directory sizing display.
* Line 124 added for denial of FTP if the user dir is full.
* Line 127 added for denial of uploads if use uploads are not allowed.
@endnode

@node v2_11 "CINS v2.11"


Changes from v2.10 (Dec 15 1996) are:

CINS:
* Minor code changes to allow for easier manipulations of menu code in the
  future.  There should soon be a menu code rewrite now.  The code has been
  sufficiently modified to make such a task easier to accomplish.
* IRC added into the shell mode.  This works in the normal manner of most
  Unix like IRC command lines, of IRC [nick] [server].  Without a server
  specified, the user will be connected to the default IRC server defined in
  the config.  Without specifying a nick, they will be prompted for one, and
  get the IRC server menu as well.
* Archie added to the shell.  Just puts them in the menuing interface for it
  at the moment.
* IRC code changed around a bit to better allow for future expansions and
  changes.  The stupid menuing system for IRC should be the first one to
  receive the new menuing system when I have it finished.
* IRC in hotkey mode was not selecting a server if the user just hit return
  at the server menu.  Fixed.
* Program graphics files (those from the Menus/ and Text/ directories) now
  are handled as CNet's own SysText: files; with the (sys|tt[1-4]).filename
  convention.

CINS.cfg,CINS.cmd,CINS.txt:
* Moved into CINS:Cfg/ directory for general tidiness.

Archie.serv,IRC.serv:
* Renamed without .serv extension, and moved into CINS:Cfg/ for general
  tidiness.

Longtime.txt,News.txt,IRC.txt:
* Renamed without the .txt extension and moved into CINS:Text/ for general
  tidiness, and usage with the sys|tt# filenaming convention.

Menus/:
* Now uses the sys|tt# filename convention to allow for multiple menu
  options for the different terminal types.
@endnode

@node v2_10 "CINS v2.10"


Changes from v2.9(Dec  4 1996) are:

ALL:
* Minor code optimizations migrated across all modules.  (When coding, one
  sometimes see spots code can be made better, but doesn't make the change to
  all possible locations.  That's all this means.  =)

CINS:
* Better defaults set for FTP prefs, instead of all off.
* Now uses bbstext line 2133 for sendmail instead of hardcoded, in the
  CNet/4 version.  The CNet/3 version retains the hardcoded sendmail call.

CINSEdit:
* Better defaults set for FTP prefs, instead of all off.
* Ghosted entries in VDE are now truly ghosted.  No more \c0.  (Thanks,
  Bob!)

CINSMaint:
* First incarnation of the Maintenance utility.  Just run it as an AmigaDOS
  executable with an argument of how many days old a file must be to be
  deleted due to age.  Be _very_ careful with this utility, as it does
  delete those files with no warning.  If you have any worries about it,
  @{b}DO NOT USE IT!@{ub}

CINS.txt:
* Line 132 added for name to be used for Archie sent email.
* Line 133 added for subject of Archie sent email.

CINS.cmd:
* Archie path/name is now definable.  This is only for the path/name, however.
  No {#4 used or needed.
@endnode

@node v2_9 "CINS v2.9"


Changes from v2.8(Nov 29 1996) are:

CINSCfg:
* Now handles the creation of all VDEs for CINS.  It will make its VDE and
  update the UCfg VDE after it is run.
* New directive for which line the CINS specific lines in bbstext start.  The
  line to put in the BBSText start is the initial CINS comment line.
  (2250 as default in the distribution)

CINSEdit:
* Addition of option to bypass mget prompt.
* Expert mode and auto-muffle were transposed in the VDE.  Fixed.
* bbsmenus 49 and 50 are GONE.  Those lines are now handled by the lines
  added to bbstext in the "add_to_bbstext" file.  Set the bbstext start
  value in CINSCfg to the initial added line to bbstext.

CINS-VDE:
* @{b}REMOVED@{ub} as its functionality was replaced by CINSCfg.

CINS.txt:
* Lines 46 and 153 changed for addition of mget option to FTP prefs.
* Line 45 changed as I made a stupid mistake.  Forgot to double the %'s as a
  single one will just get eaten.
* Lines 135-137 and 140-143 are now obsolete as they have moved into bbstext.

ETC:
* Moved ? help menus from SysText:Menu/CINS#? to CINS:Menu/CINS#?.
@endnode

@node v2_8 "CINS v2.8"


Changes from v2.7(Nov 24 1996) are:

CINS:
* Shell mode now automatically entered if the user has "Auto-Shell" prefs
  option on.

CINS-VDE:
* Main CINS Config VDE is now in SysText:VDE/CINS/CINS.
* New User Config VDE (SysText:VDE/CINS/UCfg).

CINSDir:
* bbsmenu for CINSDir is now only one over the main CINS bbsmenu.  (if CINS
  is menu 42, CINSDir is menu 43)

CINSEdit:
* bbsmenu for main CINSEdit *REMOVED*.  Its functionality has been rendered
  useless with the new hotkey prefs settings.
* New option to directly enter shell mode on entering of CINS.
* Muffle other ports is now a user definable option.
* If a user has full ANSI support, they will have a VDE option for their
  prefs.
* Two bbsmenus are now needed by CINSEdit.  Menus 49 and 50 are now required
  for the VDE operation, and those numbers are required at this point.  I
  would like to not need two menus, and not require them to be numbered, but
  the only solution I can see to it is acquiring a section of bbstext.

CINS.cfg:
* MUFF= directive removed from global config file as it has moved to a user
  configurable option.

CINS.txt:
* Lines 36-38, 40-43 updated to fix bug in CINSEdit of not saving user
  NcFTP prefs.
* Line 60 added as a general purpose file error message.
* Lines 130-131, 160-163 added to support new CINSEdit options, and interface.
* Lines 155-156 were backwards, they should be 155: Off; and 156: On.
@endnode

@node v2_7 "CINS v2.7"


Changes from v2.6(Nov 22 1996) are:

CINS:
* Accounting system bug in rate type conversion introduced with CINSCfg
  fixed.
* Accounting now handles fractions of a minute correctly.
* Internal handling of configuration variables cleaned up a tad.

CINSCFg:
* Accounting rate now writes its correct value to the config file.
* Default IRC, Gopher and Archie servers are handled in the VDE.

CINSDir:
* Internal handling of configuration variables cleaned up a tad.

CINSEdit:
* Internal handling of configuration variables cleaned up a tad.

CINS.txt:
* Lines 60, 115, and 122 were removed as their functionality moved into the
  VDE config.

CINS-VDE:
* Change in the Rate setting entry to fix the accounting error.
* Addition of default IRC, Archie, and Gopher servers.
@endnode

@node v2_6 "CINS v2.6"


Changes from v2.5(Nov 20 1996) are:

CINS:
* New command from hotkey interface: "!"  This allows those with full system
  maintenance to use the CINSCfg interface.

CINSCfg:
* New module to setup CINS configuration options.

CINS-VDE:
* Program to create the CINS VDE file.

CINS.cmd:
* Command #15 added to support CINSCfg utility.

CINS.guide:
* Initial version of the .guide version of the documentation.  It's not
  complete yet, but it's getting there.
@endnode

@node v2_5 "CINS v2.5"


Changes from v2.4b(Nov 19 1996) are:

@{b}NOTE:@{ub} New CINS: assign @{b}required@{ub}!

CINS:
* Now uses the assign CINS: to find all data files.  If anyone has a better
  idea of making it configurable, and have it work from the resident list,
  please let me know.
* If CINS:Telnet/Menu or CINS:FTP/Menu are not present, the Telnet or FTP
  program will be launched with no argument from the hotkey mode. (4.x only)

CINSDir:
* Cleaned up output on the "Current working directory is" line.
* Implemented CINS: assign in the code.

CINSEdit:
* Implemented CINS: assign in the code.
@endnode

@node v2_4b "CINS v2.4b"


Changes from v2.4a(Nov 18 1996) are:

CINSDir:
* New CD command added.  CD .. is the method to go back a directory.  This
  function should not let a user go below their home directory.  If it does,
  please let me know ASAP.
* CD added to bottom of the CINSDir bbsmenu.

CINS.txt:
* Line 127 changed to {}, as that line's functionality was replaced with
  only bbstext calls.
* Line 125 changed to support the new CD command in CINSDir.
@endnode

@node v2_4a "CINS v2.4a"


Changes from v2.4(Nov 16 1996) are:

CINSDir:
* Fixed a potential security problem with allowing /'s to be used for file
  tagging/reading/etc.
* Fixed handling of filenames containing numbers in them.
@endnode

@node v2_4 "CINS v2.4"


Changes from v2.3(Nov 15 1996) are:

CINS:
* Preliminary gopher support added.  Line 121-122 added to CINS.txt for
  support of this addition, as well as a change to command function 12
  in CINS.cmd.  This is currently designed to work with my preliminary
  CNetC version of the BBGopher code, but should work with any gopher
  client that handles command line arguments the same way.
* CINS is now resident-able code.

CINSDir:
* CINSDir is now resident-able code.

CINSEdit:
* CINSEdit is now resident-able code.

BBGopher:
* CNetC version of the bbgopher program.  Changes from original docs are:
  * Config file is in SysData:bbgopher.conf
  * There is no online helpfile as of yet, I'm working on it.
* This one is definately beta, so if you have any problems with it, let me
  know, please.
@endnode

@node v2_3 "CINS v2.3"


Changes from v2.2(Nov 11 1996) are:

CINS:
* Memory usage for loading of CINS.txt file now really uses a format like
  bbstext.  Memory used by CINS.txt is now sizeof(CINS.txt) + 4 * lines.

CINSDir:
* Now uses CINS.txt for most output.

CINSEdit:
* Now uses CINS.txt for most output.

CINS.txt:
* Lines 121-159 added to CINS.txt for external modules CINSDir and CINSEdit
* Line 44 changed to allow the NcFTP prompt to move to line 45 for future
  expansion.
* Line 2 changes for NcFTP edit prefs, and general usage.
@endnode

@node v2_2 "CINS v2.2"


Changes from v2.1(Nov 10 1996) are:

CINS:
* Internal accounting system to make up for the lack of "minutes of use of
  pfile" option in Config/Accounting.

ALL:
* IDLE line removed from CINS.cfg as it wasn't being used anymore.
* RATE line added to CINS.cfg dealing with accounting rate in $.01/minute
  increments.
* Line 108 added to CINS.txt to handle accounting output.
* Lines 2 and 3 removed from CINS.txt as I moved those into the Menus/Main
  file.

ALSO:
* A 3.x version of CINS is also available.  The only difference is it's
  compiled with 3.x headers, and handles the user UUCP id requirements of
  not being a number.
@endnode

@node v2_1 "CINS v2.1"


Changes from v2.0 are:

CINS:
* Few more optimizations, and complete implementation of the CINS.cmd file.
* Most of the program text is now external in Doors:CINS/CINS.txt.
  Treat this file as though it were bbstext, cuz it works like it!
* Removed the final goto from the original code!

CINS.cmd:
* Added line for iuumail.

ALL:
* Changed the version string format a tad.
* bbsmenu everywhere functions (#2) now parse correctly in all modules.
* Couple more optimizations.
@endnode

@node v2_0 "CINS v2.0"


Changes from v1.0 are:

CINS:
* Numerous optimizations, and removal of unneccesary code.
* Help and main hotkeyed section code no longer runs recursively.
  Could cause problems in the earlier versions, where it might take a
  few attempts to exit the help functions.
* Shell mode enabled, more or less.  Archie, IRC, and Gopher are not
  enabled in the shell currently.  I do plan on having them in by v3.0
  at the latest.
* Shell mode uses bbsmenu for command handling.  I would like to talk to
  Ray to double check on aliases, command parsing, etc. to cover all the
  bases to make sure it's all working.
* New config file: Doors:CINS/CINS.cmd
  Contains the command lines for the programs, ala bbstext.  Same with
  bbstext, don't change the line order!!

CINSEdit:
* Recursively runnable funtions de-recursived.
* bbsmenu addition for commands. (#43 in default, is config defined menu + 1)

CINSDir:
* Recursively runnable funtions de-recursived.
* bbsmenu addition for commands. (#44 in default, is config defined menu + 2)
* All DOS command dependancies removed from the code.
* DIR shows a quick C:Dir command like display.  While List will work like
  a direct access directory. (I may end up just leeching off of that menu
  instead ;)

ALL:
* Help files for SysText:Menu/  If you'd rather see these remain in CINS/ let
  me know.
* Menu files moved to CINS/Menus/ for future expansion and organization
  reasons.
* Config file (CINS.cfg) has new options in it:
       URL=<default web page>
       MENU=<number of bbsmenu containing the command set for shell>
@endnode

@node v1_0 "CINS v1.0"


First version of CINS after conversion and recoding of the old Proteus code by
Steve Fraden.
@endnode

@node Future "The Future of CINS"


    Where to from here?

       Better Help - Better online help files for the Help function.
              CINS - Ability to disable commands based on access level.
         CINSMaint - Add a few additional functions.
       CINSControl - A single server to handle CINS processes, and data flow.
@endnode

